<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles: O.J. Simpson</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<P>In the first day of his three-day deposition, Brian "Kato" Kaelin talks about his relationship with O.J. and Nicole Brown Simpson, the couple's violent relationship, and events leading up to the murders. Simpson was angry with his former wife for "playing hardball" with him in granting access to their children, Kato recalls. In the days following the murders, one of Simpson's friends says to Kaelin, "It's O.J., man.  Get your story straight."</P>
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<PRE>
SUPERIOR COURT OF THE STATE OF CALIFORNIA 
FOR THE COUNTY OF LOS ANGELES 
 
SHARON RUFO, 
Plaintiff, 
 
v.  
 
ORENTHAL JAMES SIMPSON et al.,  
Defendants 
 
FREDRIC GOLDMAN,  
Plaintiffs, 
 
vs. 
 
ORENTHAL JAMES SIMPSON, et al., 
Defendants 
 
LOUIS H. BROWN, etc., 
Plaintiffs, 
 
vs. 
 
ORENTHAL JAMES SIMPSON, 
Defendant. 
 
Videotaped deposition of ORENTHAL JAMES SIMPSON, taken 
on behalf of the Plaintiffs, at 11377 West Olympic Boulevard, 10th 
Floor, Los Angeles, California, commencing at 9:40 a.m., on 
Wednesday, February 14, 1996, before David S. Coleman, CSR 
#4613, pursuant to Court Order. 
 
