Simpson spent time with his children? 
 
A. Yes. I observed them together. 
 
Q. And how often, based on your observations, did Mr. Simpson 
spend time with the children? 
 
A. When he was in town he would free his schedule briefly. He 
didn't - 
 
Q. Was he out of town often? 
 
A. He was out of town often. He didn't - he didn't spend a lot of 
time with his children unless Nicole was around. 
 
Q. Would the children, on weekends, for example, stay with Mr. 
Simpson and not with Nicole? 
 
A. Rarely. 
 
Q. So based on your relationship with Nicole, you observed that 
she had the children virtually every day? 
 
MR. LEONARD: Object to the leading. 
 
A. Nicole - 
 
Q. What was your observations [sic] as far as how often Nicole had 
the children? 
 
A. My observation was that I felt Nicole had the responsibility of 
both mother and father because she often had the children every 
weekend. I mean, it was rare that O.J. actually took them and kept 
them for more than a day. 
 
Q. When you say "every weekend," did she also have them during 
the week? 
 
A. Yes, she did. She had them all the time, essentially. I used to 
tell her, it was as if she didn't have an ex-husband. 
 
Q. Did Nicole and you ever have conversations about Mr. 
Simpson's time with the children or lack of time? 
 
A. Yes. 
 
Q. Could you relate those discussions? 
 
A. Nicole always felt that she could never make weekend plans 
unless she had a babysitter because she could never count on O.J. 
to keep his word and keep the children on their committed - on his 
committed time. As much as Nicole adored her children and she - 
she didn't mind the fact that he would bring them back - everybody 
needs their free time - and Nicole felt it was unfair. 
 
