The prosecution challenges the findings of a defense expert who concluded that Erik Menendez suffers from Post Traumatic Stress Disorder.</P>

<P><A HREF="ts14.html">Trial Summary: Week 14</A><BR>
The defense presents testimony to corroborate Erik Menendez's claims of abuse.</P>

<P><A HREF="ts13.html">Trial Summary: Week 13</A><BR>
After 15 days on the witness stand, Erik Menendez completes his testimony.</P>

<P><A HREF="ts12.html">Trial Summary: Week 12</A><BR>
The prosecution continues its cross-examination of Erik Menendez.</P>

<P><A HREF="ts11.html">Trial Summary: Week 11</A><BR>
Prosecutor David Conn challenges Erik Menendez's testimony about the events leading up to the fatal shootings of Jose and Kitty Menendez.</P>

<P><A HREF="ts10.html">Trial Summary: Week 10</A><BR>
Erik Menendez testifies about his relationship with his parents and the events that led up to their murder.</P>

<P><A HREF="ts09.html">Trial Summary: Week 9</A><BR>
Erik Menendez takes the witness stand.</P>

<P><A HREF="ts08.html">Trial Summary: Week 8</A><BR>
The defense continues its attack on the prosecution reconstruction of the crime sccene.</P>

<P><A HREF="ts07.html">Trial Summary: Week 7</A><BR>
The prosecution rests its case-in-chief. The defense attacks the credibility of a key prosecution witness.</P>

<P><A HREF="ts06.html">Trial Summary: Week 6</A><BR>
The defense attacks the credibility and reliability of key prosecution witness Roger McCarthy.</P>

<P><A HREF="ts05.html">Trial Summary: Week 5</A><BR>
The state presents evidence to prove the murders were premeditated.</P>

<P><A HREF="ts04.html">Trial Summary: Week 4</A><BR>
Friends and family of the Menendez brothers testify against them.</P>

<P><A HREF="ts03.html">Trial Summary: Week 3</A><BR>
Witnesses say the Menendez brothers tried to fabricate evidence.</P>

<P><A HREF="ts02.html">Trial Summary: Week 2</A><BR>
The prosecution presents evidence to support its theory that greed motivated the Menendez brothers to kill their parents.</P>

