<H2>Administrative Hearing for Barry Feinstein (1/93)</H2>

<P>Barry Feinstein, the president of the New York chapter of the Teamsters, was charged with embezzling $500,000 of union funds for his personal use. Feinstein had reached a plea-bargain agreement to dismiss civil corruption charges against him. The agreement, however, was rejected by an administrative judge. Feinstein subsequently agreed to a lifetime banishment from all of his Teamsters' union posts and was ordered repay $104,000 to Teamsters Local 237.</P>
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/rights2.gif" ALT="Copyright 1996 by American Lawyer Media, L.P. All Rights Reserved.">
