<H2>Arizona v. Salman (5/94)</H2>

<P>Frank Salman, 18, was charged with second-degree murder and three counts of aggravated assault and his cousin, John Salman, 20, was charged with four counts of aggravated assault for the shooting death of Larry Sanchez, one of several gang members who robbed the Salmans' family convenience store.</P>

<P>Frank and John Salman, who were working at the store on the night of the robbery, pursued and shot the fleeing thieves, killing Sanchez. The prosecution argued the cousins used "excessive force" in response to the crime. The defense contended the cousins acted in self-defense.</P>

<P><b>Verdict</B><br>
The judge deadlocked and the judge declared a mistrial.</P>
