<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A></P>
<p><H2>Askew v. Askew (4/93)</H2>


Ronald and Bonette Askew were experiencing problems after 15 years of marriage so they went to a marriage counselor. Bonette Askew revealed during a session that she never really loved her husband. He sued his estranged wife for fraud, claiming if she hadn't lied about loving him, he would not have married her and wouldn't be dividing their property as part of the divorce. Bonette Askew's attorney said Ronald was trying to get around California's no-fault divorce laws.<p>

<b>Verdict</b><br>
The jury found for Ronald Askew and awarded him $242,000 in damages.<P>

