<p><h2>Briskin v. Briskin (1/94</h2>
Alan and Gigi Briskin, who divorced after five years of marriage, asked a West Palm Beach, Florida, judge to decide in what faith their three-year-old daughter should be raised.<p>

Gigi Briskin, who had custody of the child, converted from Catholicism to Judaism before her marriage and subsequently returned to Catholicism. She wanted to raise the child ecumenically while her husband wanted the child raised in the Jewish faith.<p>

<b>Verdict</b><br>
The judge declared the child Jewish. He ordered Gigi Briskin to raise her as a Jew and enjoined her from promoting other religions.<p>

<p>
