<HEAD>
<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A>
<H2>California v. Cummings (7/94)</H2>

<P>Debra Sue Cummings, a 36-year-old mother of two and respected member of the community, was charged in the death of a baby boy she was caring for in an unlicensed baby-sitting service. Cummings was being retried for the June 1990 death of 9-month-old Kevin Majoy-Young. He died from a severe blow to the head. Cummings testified that the boy was fatally injured when he accidentally struck his head against a living room table. She was charged with second-degree murder, voluntary manslaughter and child absue. The first trial ended in a mistrial after the jury deadlocked 7-5 in favor of acquittal.</P>

<P><B>Verdict</B><BR>
Cummings was acquitted of all charges on July 28, 1994.</P>
