<HEAD>
<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A>
<H2>California v. Lyle and Erik Menendez (1994 and 1996)</H2>

<P>Lyle and Erik Menendez were charged with murder for the August 1989 shotgun slayings of their parents in the family's Beverly Hills mansion.</P>

<P>The brothers admitted killing their parents, Jose, 45, and Kitty, 47, as the couple watched television in their living room den on August 20, 1989. They shot their father several times in the head and wounded their mother. Lyle then went to the trunk of his car, reloaded his 12-gauge shotgun and returned inside to shoot his mother several more times.</P>

<P>The prosecutors contended the brothers killed in order to get their hands on the family's $14 million fortune. The brothers claimed that they feared for the lives after suffering through a lifetime of physical,  emotional and sexual abuse by their parents.</P>

<P><B>Verdict</B><br>
The juries deadlocked and mistrials were declared in January 1994.<P>

<P>After a second trial,the brothers were convicted of first-degree murder on March 20, 1996. A jury recommended that they be sentenced to life in prison.</P>
