<HEAD>
<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A>
<H2>Corkery v. Cosby (8/94)</H2>

<P>Richard Corkery, a photographer with the New York Daily News, sued Bill Cosby for $3 million in damages, claiming the television star assaulted him during a 1992 charity event at the Metropolitan Museum of Art. He claimed Cosby dragged him out of the museum auditorium and threw him into the lobby. Cosby admitted getting into an altercation with Corkery but denied assaulting him. When his wife stood to receive an award from the Coalition of 100 Black Women, Cosby said Corkery snapped his picture without his permission. Cosby said he and a security guard then led Corkery into the museum lobby.</P>

<P><B>Verdict</B><BR>
On August 5, 1994, a federal court jury ruled Cosby must pay $2 to Corkery. The jury found Cosby liable for the assault but said Corkery was 90 percent responsible for provoking Cosby. On September 7, a judge reduced the award to 20 cents.</P>
