<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A>
<H2>Florida v. Griffin</H2>

<P>Michael F. Griffin, a 32-year-old chemical plant worker, was charged with murder for the shooting death of Dr. David Gunn during an anti-abortion protest outside an abortion clinic in Pensacola, Florida in March of 1993.  The defense argued that Griffin, a fundamentalist Christian, was delusional and acted in the heat of passion, and therefore could not be convicted of premeditated murder.</P>

<P><B>Verdict:</B><BR>
Griffin was convicted on March 6, 1994 of first-degree murder and sentenced to life in prison. He must serve 25 years before he's eligible for parole.</P>
