<HEAD>
<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A>
<H2>Florida v. Gudinas (5/95)</H2>

<P>Thomas Gudinas was charged with the May 24, 1994 murder of Michele McGrath, a 27-year-old Martin Marietta Corp. clerk and former high school homecoming queen.

<P>Gudinas, a Massachusetts man in trouble with the law since about age 10, allegedly attacked McGrath as she walked to her car after a night on the club scene in downtown Orlando. The evidence included Gudinas' palm print on the alley gate, his fingerprints on a bank payment book in McGrath's car and several eyewitnesses who said they saw him near the murder scene in the morning.</P>

<P>The defense argued that the case against the 21-year-old Gudinas was circumstantial and filled with contradictions. Among other things, the defense pointed out that laboratory tests on blood, semen and saliva could not determine the killer's identity.</P>

<P><B>Verdict</B><BR>
Gudinas was found guilty of first-degree murder and two counts of sexual battery on May 4, 1995. The jury recommended that he be sentenced to die in the electric chair.</P>
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/rights2.gif" ALT="Copyright 1996 by American Lawyer Media, L.P. All Rights Reserved.">
