<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>Florida v. Lopez (9/95)</H2>

<P>Peter Lopez was charged with first-degree murder in the fatal shooting of Scott Haak outside of a Fort Lauderdale nightspot.</P>

<P>The incident began on January 20, 1994, when Lopez and two friends were caught trying to sneak into a concert at the Mud House, a Fort Lauderdale cafe. As they were thrown out, a crowd gathered, sparking a heated argument. Some of those involved threatened Lopez.</P>

<P>Lopez drove away from the club, only to return with a shotgun. When he found one of the men who had threatened him, Lopez, 19, brandished his weapon and told Haak: "Now beat my ass."</P>

<P>Haak started toward Lopez. The gun went off and Haak was shot. Though mortally wounded, Haak pulled a small caliber handgun from a holster in his pants and managed to fire several shots at Lopez. None of the shots hit Lopez or his companions.  </P>

<P>Lopez told police that he didn't mean to shoot anyone. He said he went back to the concert to scare the people who had told him to leave. He said he recognized Haak and several others and that was why he approached them.</P>

<P><b>Verdict</b><br>
On September 7, 1995, a Broward County jury rejected the prosecutor's arguments that the killing was premeditated and convicted Lopez of manslaughter. Lopez was sentenced to seven years in prison.</P>
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/rights2.gif" ALT="Copyright 1996 by American Lawyer Media, L.P. All Rights Reserved.">
