<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A></P>

<h2>Georgia v. Horn (5/96)</h2>

Alicia Horn was charged with two counts of first-degree vehicular homicide and one count of serious injury with a motor vehicle in connection with a car crash that took the lives of an off-duty police officer and his wife, and broke the neck of their eight-month-old daughter. <p>

Prosecutors charged that Horn had injected cocaine before the accident. The defense claimed Horn suffers from a severe bi-polar disorder and that her mental state contributed to causing the accident.<p>

<b>Verdict</b><br>
Horn pleaded guilty and was sentenced to 17 years in prison followed by 18 years probation. Horn can not drive a car while on probation. She also was fined $1,000.<p>

<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/rights2.gif" ALT="Copyright 1996 by American Lawyer Media, L.P. All Rights Reserved.">
