<H2>Horn v. Highline Community Hospital (3/95)</H2>

<P>Highline Community Hospital and three doctors were sued for medical malpractice in connection with the withdrawal of life support (food and water) from patient Scott Horn for five days in December 1993.</P>

<P>Kate Kaemerle, Horn's ex-wife, alleged the doctors and the hospital illegally and improperly withdrew Horn's life support and sued for the suffering and fear Horn endured during the five days before food and water were restored.</P>

<P>Horn's family and the doctors had come to the conclusion that Horn was in a long-term vegetative state with very little hope of recovery. Kaemerle maintained that her ex-husband was conscious and cognitive, but only could communicate by blinking his eyes.</P>

<P><b>Verdict</b><br>
On March 31, 1995, the jury found for the defendants on all counts.</P>
