<H2>Kentucky v. Pleasant (1/94)</H2>

<P>Typhanie Pleasant, 21, was charged with the murder of her newborn son, who was born January 1, 1993. Pleasant, who lived at home but kept the pregnancy a secret from her parents, claimed the baby developed breathing problems shortly after birth. After her efforts to administer artificial respiration failed, she said she wrapped up the baby and placed him in a garbage can. The prosecution contended Pleasant suffocated the baby.</P>

<P><B>Verdict</B><BR>
A jury convicted Pleasant of second-degree murder on January 31, 1994.</P>
