<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A>
<H2>Massachusetts v. Manning (6/94)</H2>

<P>The Rev. Paul Manning was charged with molesting an 11-year-old altar boy. The main witness against Manning was another priest, the Rev. Paul Sughrue. He testified that on Sept. 5, 1993, he heard several screams and climbed the stairs to Manning's study at the rectory of St. Charles Church in Woburn. He said Manning and the boy had their pants down and were clinging together and making a rocking motion.</P>

<P>Manning denied the charges, testifying there was no nudity and that he and the boy were only involved in horseplay.</P>

<P><B>Verdict</B><BR>
A jury acquitted Manning on June 25, 1994.</P>
