<HEAD>
<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A></P>
<p><h2>McWherter v. City of Ann Arbor (9/95)</h2>
Lois McWherter, an Arbor Arbor, Michigan, parking official sued the city and two co-workers for sexual harassment. McWherter claimed a colleague, Dean Bowerbank, harassed her and when she complained to John Avendt, her supervisor, he forced her to work closely with Bowerbank and have her poor evaluations.<p>

Bowerbank maintained he did not harass her, despite the findings of an internal investigation, and the city and Avendt claimed Bowerbank was punished for his actions and behavior.<p>

<b>Verdict</b><br>
The jury found for McWherter and awarded her a total of $255,000 -- $35,000 from Avendt and $220,000 from the city. The jury found that Bowerbank did not harass her.<p>

<p>
