<HEAD>
<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A></P>
<p><h2>Michigan v. Cato Riggs (5/94)</h2>

Toni Cato Riggs was charged with first-degree murder and conspiracy for her role in the death of her husband, Anthony Riggs, a serviceman who was fatally shot a few weeks after returning from the Persian Gulf War. Prosecutors claimed she had him killed to collect on a $150,000 insurance policy. After the murder, <a href=/report/catoriggs.html> Cato Riggs </a> allegedly got involved in a drug smuggling operation and confessed to undercover agents posing as drug dealers that she planned her husband's death. The defense claimed she made the statements in order to impress the agents she thought were tough drug kingpins.<p>

<b>Verdict</b><br>
Cato Riggs was found guilty of first-degree murder and conspiracy to commit murder. She was sentenced to life in prison without parole.<p>

<p>
