<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A>
<H2>Michigan v. Younes (4/96)</H2>

<P>Scott  Younes,  a Detroit gang member, was charged with first-degree murder in the fatal shooting of a Detroit police officer.</P>

<P>Prosecutors claimed he was seeking revenge for an earlier gang skirmish when he shot and killed Officer Jerry Philpot on May 25, 1995.</P>

<P>Here's what happened.</P>

<P>Mike Lopez  was visiting his friend Geneva Mendoza, when they decided to go to a neighborhood store to buy some gum. As they neared the store, they were confronted by four or five young men believed to be members of the Latin Counts gang. The gang members started beating up Lopez and Mendoza ran home to tell her father, Teddy McClellan. </P>

<P>After Philpot and his partner arrived at McClellan's house to investigate the incident, McClellan and his son, Teddy Mendoza, went out into the streets and located one of Lopez's assailants -- Victor Salinas.  Mendoza beat him up. The police officers heard about the fight and showed up the scene. Salinas was taken into custody.</P>

<P>In the meantime, gang members drove by McClellan's house, threatening to shoot his house down. The prosecution claimed Younes, who lived in the neighborhood, told McClellan,  "you shouldn't have gotten involved...your house will go down."</P>

<P>A short time later, some of Salinas' friends, including Younes, and family members showed up at the police station. It was then that Younes and John Kolniak decided to avenge Salinas' beating. Kolniak would shoot up McClellan's house and Younes would back him up in case there were problems, according to prosecutors.</P>

<P>The two police officers, in the meantime, realized that they had lost a flashlight and went back to McClellan's house to get it.  </P>

<P>When they got near the house, they heard gunshots. The officers spotted  Kolniak, carrying a long gun.   Kolniak faced the officers. Philpot and his partner drew their guns.  The officers fired as Kolniak tried to aim at the officers.  Kolniak was fatally wounded.</P>

<P>Then as the officers approached, Younes fired numerous shots with a semiautomatic assault rifle. One shot struck Philpot.</P>

<P>The defense conceded that Younes fired a shot. But it insisted there was no evidence that he planned to kill Philpot and therefore was not guilty of premeditated murder.</P>

<P><b>Verdict</b><br>
On April 23, 1996, a jury found Younes guilty of first-degree murder. He was sentenced to life in prison without parole.</P>
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/rights2.gif" ALT="Copyright 1996 by American Lawyer Media, L.P. All Rights Reserved.">
