<HEAD>
<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A>
<H2>Missouri v. Neeley (11/94)</H2>

<P>Paul Neeley, 39, was charged with second-degree murder in the 
March 14, 1994 shooting of Mike Terrell, his former best friend. 
Neeley said he killed Terrell after his 16-year-old daughter told 
him that Terrell had raped her several years earlier. 
The prosecution claimed Neeley killed Terrell simply for revenge. 
The defense argued Neeley was not guilty because he was 
suffering from a mental disease or defect, or that, at the very 
least, Neeley's actions were the result of a sudden passion 
brought on by the news of the rape, and was therefore guilty only 
of voluntary manslaughter.</P>

<P><B>Verdict</B><BR>
On November 18, 1994, a jury found Neeley guilty of second-degree murder.</P>
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/rights2.gif" ALT="Copyright 1996 by American Lawyer Media, L.P. All Rights Reserved.">
