<HEAD>
<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A>
<H2>Roberts v. Scheriff (5/95)</H2>

<P>The atmosphere at the prestigious Denver Athletic Club turned nasty when several members of the 100-year-old facility started complaining about manager Glenn Roberts.</P>

<P>One thing led to another. First, a flier showed up in the members' lockers depicting Roberts as Hitler and Mickey Mouse.  Several subsequent fliers and cartoons accused him of racial and sexual discrimination and of financially benefiting from staff cuts at the facility.</P>

<P>Roberts, a retired Air Force lieutenant colonel who ran officers' clubs in the military before joining the Denver Athletic Club in 1988, sued Martin Scheriff for defamation. The suit sought $3 million in damages.</P>

<P>During the trial, Roberts testified that the fliers and cartoons harmed his reputation among club members and other club managers and caused him to develop medical problems, including high blood pressure. Roberts also accused Scheriff of calling the Internal Revenue Service suggesting that the agency investigate Roberts.</P>

<P>Scheriff, who represented himself, denied calling the IRS or having anything to do with the fliers and cartoons. He claimed Roberts targeted him because Scheriff circulated petitions calling for the disclosure of Roberts' salary and terms of his contract. In 1993, Scheriff and other members asked the club's board of directors to halt a vote to extend Roberts' contract and to obtain information on how he was paid. The board rejected the request and voted to extend Roberts' contact.</P>

<P>Several club members claimed that the athletic facilities, food and service at the club had deteriorated under Roberts' leadership.</P>

<P><b>Verdict</b><br>
On June 2, 1995, a Denver district court jury awarded $5,000 to Roberts.</P>
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/rights2.gif" ALT="Copyright 1996 by American Lawyer Media, L.P. All Rights Reserved.">
<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/frontpage/spacer.gif" ALT="No parts of this site may be reproduced without permission of American Lawyer Media." BORDER="0">
