<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A></P>
<p><h2>Shanes-Hernandez v. Clementoni (11/94)</H2>
Gigi Shanes-Hernandez, a 37-year-old white woman employed as an employment coordinator in the Westchester (N.Y.) County Office of Employment and Training, claimed she was sexually harassed by her co-worker, Lawrence Cunningham, a black male. She said she reported each incident of harassment to her superior and to the county Office of Affirmative Action but that no action was taken. <p>

The county argued Cunningham's behavior may have been playful and inappropriate but it was not harassment. The defense also denied Shane-Hernandez's allegations that the county tried to fire her after she filed a complaint with the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission.<p>

<b>Verdict</b><br>
A federal court jury found for Shanes-Hernandez and awarded her $285,000 in compensatory damages.<p>

<p>
