<HEAD>
<TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>Sylvestre v. Alvarez (11/95)</H2>

<P>Wendy Sylvestre sued obstetrician Victor Alvarez and the Holmes (Florida) Regional Medical Center for negligence on behalf of her four-year-old brain-damaged daughter.</P>

<P>Sylvestre claimed the low blood sugar level that led to Ashley Gerber's brain damage was caused by an infection passed between her and her daughter prior to delivery. Sylvestre's lawyers claimed Alvarez should have warned the pediatrician caring for the child that a low- grade fever and vomiting Sylvestre had two days before she left the hospital might have been caused by an infection. If he had notified the pediatrician, they argued, Ashley could have been kept at the hospital longer and the blood sugar problem would have been detected before it caused brain damage.</P>

<P>Alvarez contended that Sylvestre and Ashley were healthy when they left the hospital, and it would have been impossible to predict the child's condition would deteriorate so quickly.</P>

<P>Sylvestre's lawsuit sought $13.45 million in damages -- enough to pay for her daughter's care for the rest of her life.</P>

<P><b>Verdict</b><br>
Wendy Sylvestre received $850,000 from the Holmes Regional Medical Center. In early November, the hospital agreed to settle the case for $350,000 provided that the jury found Alvarez liable. If the jury found for Alvarez, the hospital obligated itself to pay an additional $500,000.</P>

<P>On November 15, 1995, the jury took less than an hour to decide that Alvarez was not responsible for Ashley Gerber's physical and mental retardation.</P>
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/rights2.gif" ALT="Copyright 1996 by American Lawyer Media, L.P. All Rights Reserved.">
<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/frontpage/spacer.gif" ALT="No parts of this site may be reproduced without permission of American Lawyer Media." BORDER="0">
<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/frontpage/spacer.gif" ALT="Nothing in this site is intended to constitute legal advice." BORDER="0">
