<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A>

<H2>Tuomala v. Regent University (8/95)</H2>

<P>Three professors asked a court to interpret their contracts with Regent University in Virgina Beach, Virginia. The professors claimed their contracts entitled them to annual renewal unless the university determined that they breached the contract. The university, a Christian school founded by Pat Robertson, claimed the three-year rolling contract permitted the school to change its terms.</P>

<P>In May 1994, the university offered the professors a contract significantly different from the one that they had been offered in the past. The three professors refused to sign the contarct and brought the legal action.</P>

<P>A judge was asked to determine whether the professors have a type of tenure entitling them to a renewal of the original contract or whether the university has the right to change the terms even if they are satisified with the professors' performance.</P>

<P><b>Verdict</b><br>
Judge Edward Hanson ruled in favor of the university on August 29, 1995.</P>
