<p><H2>Twiggs v. Mays (8/93)</H2>

The custody battle over 14-year-old Kimberly Mays who was switched at birth with another child.<p>

Ernest and Regina Twigg asked a Florida judge to declare Kimberly their biological daughter and to award them visitation rights. Robert Mays, the man who raised Kimberly, submitted to genetic testing only after the Twiggs had promised not to seek custody. Kimberly wanted the judge to terminate the Twiggs' parental rights so that she could stay with Mays.<p>

<b>Verdict</b><br>
The judged ruled the Twiggs had no legal rights to Kimberly. The decision cleared the way for Mays to adopt her.<p>

<p>
