<P><h2>Washington v. Sousa (4/93)</h2>
Julie Sousa was accused of murder in the scalding death of her five-week-old baby. <p>

Prosecutors claimed she got drunk and dunked the baby into a sink full of nearly boiling water. Her husband, Gerald, was charged with manslaughter for letting it happen.<p>

The Sousas claimed the death was a tragic accident caused by their 2 1/2-year-old daughter who decided to give her baby sister a bath when the parents were sleeping.<p>

<b>Verdict</b><br>
The trial ended in a hung jury and a mistrial was declared. The second trial also ended in a hung jury. The Sousas were found guilty of second-degree murder following a third trial in December 1994. They each were sentenced to 123 months.<p>

<p>
